		<title>03WHISKY - FILTER BEDS</title>
		<content> The filter beds or lagoons were used  
 in the past to enable the distillery  
 effluents to seep into the rivers and 
 streams with no ill effects on fish   
 and plant life. The bacteria in the   
 beds act like those in a septic tank  
 by reducing the oxygen demand to an   
 acceptable level prior to discharge in
 the waterways. The distillery         
 maintains them. The houses and hotels 
 have their own septic tanks and are   
 not connected to the filter beds.     
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
